## Idea

A _module spectrum_ is a [[module over an algebra over an (âˆž,1)-operad]] for the [[commutative operad]]:

for $R$ an [[E-âˆž ring]] (an [[algebra over an (âˆž,1)-operad|âˆž-algebra]] over [[Comm]]), an $R$-module spectrum is a [[spectrum]] equipped with an $R$-[[action]].

## Properties

By the discussion an [[tangent (âˆž,1)-category]] we may realize $E_\infty$-modules over $R$ as objects in the [[stabilization]] of the [[over-(âˆž,1)-category]] over $R$:

+-- {: .num_prop}
###### Proposition

Let $E_\infty := Alg^{Comm}(\infty Grpd)$ be the [[(âˆž,1)-category]] of [[E-âˆž ring]]s and let $R \in E_\infty$. Then the [[stabilization]] of the [[over-(âˆž,1)-category]] over $A$ 

$$
  Stab(E_\infty/R) \simeq A Mod(Spec)
$$

is equivalentl to the category of $R$-module spectra.

=--

This is ([Lurie, cor. 1.5.15](#Lurie)).

